For a moment, Cybil could not hide her astonishment, but then because of her profession, [p]
she quickly feigned a more resolute attitude.[p]
"A little girl...[p]
No, I haven't seen her..."[p]
"When I came to after the accident, my daughter was nowhere to be seen.[p]
The passenger door was open and she was gone.[p]
Cheryl...uh, sorry, my daughter's name is Cheryl...[p]
She is a timid child, so it is hard to imagine that she headed out into this weird town alone.[p]
Plus I was there in the driver's seat...[p]
And since she gave me no warning it just doesn't make sense.[p]
Are you familiar with this area?[p]
There is no sign of anyone, and what is going on with the snow at this time of year...[p]
Just what in the world has happened in this town?"[p]
Harry spoke while sighing.[p]
"I'm afraid I don't know either.[p]
I still haven't seen anyone other than you.[p]
It's like the town is as silent as a graveyard, left without even the means to contact any neighboring towns."[p]
"I see."[p]


